James VI and I Since the latter half of the 20th century , historians have tended to revise James 's reputation and treat him as a serious and thoughtful monarch .
James VI and I In his reign , the Plantation of Ulster and British colonization of the Americas began .
James VI and I James VI and I 19 June 1566 -- 27 March 1625 was King of Scotland as James VI from 24 July 1567 and King of England and Ireland as James I from the union of the Scottish and English crowns on 24 March 1603 until his death .
James VI and I He was a major advocate of a single parliament for England and Scotland .
James VI and I In 1603 , he succeeded the last Tudor monarch of England and Ireland , Elizabeth I , who died without issue .
James VI and I After the Union of the Crowns , he based himself in England the largest of the three realms from 1603 , only returning to Scotland once in 1617 , and styled himself `` King of Great Britain and Ireland '' .
James VI and I Four different regents governed during his minority , which ended officially in 1578 , though he did not gain full control of his government until 1583 .
James VI and I Sir Anthony Weldon claimed that James had been termed `` the wisest fool in Christendom '' , an epithet associated with his character ever since .
James VI and I He continued to reign in all three kingdoms for 22 years , a period known after him as the Jacobean era , until his death in 1625 at the age of 58 .
James VI and I James succeeded to the Scottish throne at the age of thirteen months , after his mother Mary was compelled to abdicate in his favour .
James VI and I He sponsored the translation of the Bible that would later be named after him : the Authorised King James Version .
James VI and I He achieved most of his aims in Scotland but faced great difficulties in England , including the Gunpowder Plot in 1605 and repeated conflicts with the English Parliament .
James VI and I James was the son of Mary , Queen of Scots , and a great-great-grandson of Henry VII , King of England and Lord of Ireland , positioning him to eventually accede to all three thrones .
James VI and I James himself was a talented scholar , the author of works such as Daemonologie 1597 , The True Law of Free Monarchies 1598 , and Basilikon Doron 1599 .
James VI and I At 57 years and 246 days , James 's reign in Scotland was longer than those of any of his predecessors .
James VI and I Under James , the `` Golden Age '' of Elizabethan literature and drama continued , with writers such as William Shakespeare , John Donne , Ben Jonson , and Sir Francis Bacon contributing to a flourishing literary culture .
